by freezing a big batch of semi-dried tomatoes to use down the road. #driedtomatoes #ovendried #preserves #tomatoes #vegan #heynutritionlady"   class="skip-lazy a3-notlazy no-lazyload dpsp-post-pinterest-image-hidden-inner" data-no-lazy="1" /></div><div class="dpsp-post-pinterest-image-hidden" style="display: none;"><img width="680" height="1020" src="https://www.heynutritionlady.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/10-680x1020.jpg" data-pin-media="https://www.heynutritionlady.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/10.jpg"  data-pin-description="These Semi-Dried Tomatoes are amazing little flavour bombs. Oven dried tomatoes are easy to make at home, and are perfect to add to salads, sandwiches, pizza, or meal bowls. Make the most out of tomato season by freezing a big batch of semi-dried tomatoes to use down the road. #driedtomatoes #ovendried #preserves #tomatoes #vegan #heynutritionlady"   class="skip-lazy a3-notlazy no-lazyload dpsp-post-pinterest-image-hidden-inner  dpsp-post-pinterest-image-hidden-single" data-no-lazy="1" /></div><span id="dpsp-post-content-markup" data-image-pin-it="true"></span>
<p><em>These <strong>semi-dried tomatoes</strong> are rich, concentrated, and bursting with sweet tomato flavor. Slowly roasted in the oven, they&rsquo;re easy to make at home and perfect for adding to salads, sandwiches, pizzas, or grain bowls. Make a double batch and freeze them for later &mdash; a simple way to enjoy peak tomato flavor all year long.&nbsp;</em></p>


<div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="1020" data-pin-description="These Semi-Dried Tomatoes are amazing little flavour bombs. Oven dried tomatoes are easy to make at home, and are perfect to add to salads, sandwiches, pizza, or meal bowls. Make the most out of tomato season by freezing a big batch of semi-dried tomatoes to use down the road. #driedtomatoes #ovendried #preserves #tomatoes #vegan #heynutritionlady" src="https://www.heynutritionlady.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/semi_dried_tomatoes_4-680x1020.jpg" alt="A piece of toast on a blue plate topped with ricotta and semi dried tomatoes" data-skip-lazy class="wp-image-14211" srcset="https://www.heynutritionlady.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/semi_dried_tomatoes_4-680x1020.jpg 680w, https://www.heynutritionlady.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/semi_dried_tomatoes_4-720x1080.jpg 720w, https://www.heynutritionlady.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/semi_dried_tomatoes_4-360x540.jpg 360w, https://www.heynutritionlady.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/semi_dried_tomatoes_4-180x270.jpg 180w, https://www.heynutritionlady.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/semi_dried_tomatoes_4-200x300.jpg 200w, https://www.heynutritionlady.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/semi_dried_tomatoes_4-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.heynutritionlady.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/semi_dried_tomatoes_4.jpg 1067w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" data-pin-media="https://www.heynutritionlady.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/semi_dried_tomatoes_4.jpg"></figure>
</div>


<div class="wp-block-group has-background" style="background-color:#f5efdf"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-let-s-hear-it-for-semi-dried">Let's hear it for semi-dried!</h2>



<p>Ever wish you could have summer tomatoes year-round? Well, with semi-dried tomatoes, you can! </p>



<p>This is my favorite thing to do with the sad, winter tomatoes you can get in the grocery store. We're going to slow-roast them in the oven so the flavors concentrate and the sweetness shines. </p><div class="fluentform ff-default fluentform_wrapper_3 ffs_custom_wrap"><form data-form_id="3" id="fluentform_3" class="frm-fluent-form fluent_form_3 ff-el-form-top ff_form_instance_3_1 ff-form-loading ffs_custom" data-form_instance="ff_form_instance_3_1" method="POST"><fieldset style="border: none!important;margin: 0!important;padding: 0!important;background-color: transparent!important;box-shadow: none!important;outline: none!important; min-inline-size: 100%;">
