	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-136596">
	<article id="article-comment-136596">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Lauri</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">June 13, 2024 at 12:06 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://www.heynutritionlady.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
I recently came across a recipe calling for semi dried tomatoes. Never heard of them, so I googled and came across this recipe (along with premade ones for sale for a lot more money than it costs to make them yourself). I don’t think I’ll ever use sun dried tomatoes again! I’ve made at least a half dozen batches of this so far. I’ve used them to make a vinaigrette, as a topping on white pizza, and my favorite - blasting with a stick blender and a little bit of cream and adding it to marinara. So, so good!! Thank you for sharing this simple but genius recipe!</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-136596" data-commentid="136596" data-postid="14210" data-belowelement="article-comment-136596" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lauri" aria-label="Reply to Lauri">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-themuffinmyth bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-136848">
	<article id="article-comment-136848">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Katie Trant</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">July 01, 2024 at 6:54 am</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Hey Lauri, this comment made me so happy! I love all of the creative uses you've come up with for semi-dried tomatoes. I've never considered using them for a vinaigrette or a cream sauce, such tasty ideas!</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-136848" data-commentid="136848" data-postid="14210" data-belowelement="article-comment-136848" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Katie Trant" aria-label="Reply to Katie Trant">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-131128">
	<article id="article-comment-131128">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Monica</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">June 09, 2023 at 2:01 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>I’m on an extremely low sodium diet thank you so very much for this recipe which I will be making tomorrow.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-131128" data-commentid="131128" data-postid="14210" data-belowelement="article-comment-131128" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Monica" aria-label="Reply to Monica">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-themuffinmyth bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-131133">
